'''拿俄米·舍莫尔'''（{{lang-he|נעמי שמר}}，''Naomi Shemer''；1930年7月13日 - 2004年6月26日）是[[以色列|以色列]]的一位[[作曲家|作曲家]]和歌手<ref>{{cite news |title='Jerusalem of Gold,' Israel Festival Song, Strikes Gold |newspaper=Billboard |date=October 21, 1967 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=JUUEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT10&dq=%22naomi+shemer%22+leading+songwriter#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=November 28, 2010 |archive-date=2017-03-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170322025226/https://books.google.com/books?id=JUUEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PT10&dq=%22naomi+shemer%22+leading+songwriter#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>，被誉为“以色列词曲界第一夫人”。<ref>{{cite news |title=Naomi Shemer: First lady of Israeli song |first1=Sagui |last1=Ben-Nun |first2=Gidi |last2=Avivi |newspaper=Haaretz |date=June 27, 2004 |url=http://www.haaretz.com/print-edition/news/naomi-shemer-first-lady-of-israeli-song-1.126436 |accessdate=November 28, 2010 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924225155/http://www.haaretz.com/print-edition/news/naomi-shemer-first-lady-of-israeli-song-1.126436 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=A Nation Mourns Naomi Shemer, Iconic Songstress |first=Miriam |last=Colton |newspaper=Forward |date=July 2, 2004 |url=http://www.forward.com/articles/4929/ |accessdate=November 28, 2010 |archive-date=2012-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120307184845/http://forward.com/articles/4929/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>她在1967年创作的《[[金色的耶路撒冷|金色的耶路撒冷]]》成为了[[第三次中东战争|六日战争]]中的标志性歌曲。

1983年拿俄米·舍莫尔因她对[[希伯来语|希伯来语]]歌曲的贡献获得了[[以色列国家奖|以色列国家奖]]<ref name=prize>{{Cite web|title=Israel Prize Official Site – Recipients in 1983 (in Hebrew)|url=http://cms.education.gov.il/EducationCMS/Units/PrasIsrael/Tashmag/Tashnab_Tashmag_Rikuz.htm?DictionaryKey=Tashmag|access-date=2014-05-10|archive-date=2012-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120223161108/http://cms.education.gov.il/EducationCMS/Units/PrasIsrael/Tashmag/Tashnab_Tashmag_Rikuz.htm?DictionaryKey=Tashmag|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2005年在以色列{{link-en|Ynet|Ynet}}的网络评选中，她被评为“200位最伟大的以色列人”中第6位。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ynet.co.il/articles/0,7340,L-3083171,00.html |title=הישראלי מספר 1: יצחק רבין – תרבות ובידור |work=Ynet |author=גיא בניוביץ' |date=June 20, 1995 |accessdate=July 10, 2011 |archive-date=2012-09-25 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6AwLrrQK4?url=http://www.ynet.co.il/articles/0,7340,L-3083171,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==生平==
拿俄米·舍莫尔出生在[[加利利海|加利利海]]附近的一个[[基布兹|基布兹]]中，1950年代她曾在{{link-en|以色列陆军青年营|Nahal}}的文艺团中服役，后至{{link-en|耶路撒冷音乐舞蹈学院|Jerusalem Academy of Music and Dance}}学习。

她曾自己创作歌词并谱曲，也曾为著名的以色列诗歌配曲。1967年，她创作了《金色的耶路撒冷》一歌，{{link-en|舒丽·纳坦|Shuli Natan}}演唱了这首歌曲，拿俄米·舍莫尔也因此在以色列闻名。六日战争胜利后，她新创作了庆祝夺回耶路撒冷的一段，添加在原作末尾。这首歌曲“被以色列人视为非正式的第二国歌”。<ref name="Saxon">[http://www.nytimes.com/2004/06/29/arts/naomi-shemer-74-poet-and-composer-dies.html?scp=1&sq=Naomi+SHEMER&st=nyt Saxon, Wolfgang. "Naomi Shemer, 74, Poet and Composer, Dies"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2004/06/29/arts/naomi-shemer-74-poet-and-composer-dies.html?scp=1&sq=Naomi+SHEMER&st=nyt |date=20181124180212 }}, ''[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]'' obituary, 29 June 2004, accessed 3 August 2012</ref>

2004年，她因癌症逝世。她在去世前曾向朋友透露，她在创作《金色的耶路撒冷》时，借鉴了之前听到的一首[[巴斯克地區|巴斯克]]民歌《{{link-en|傻瓜约瑟夫|Pello Joxepe}}》的旋律。<ref name="Idit">[http://www.haaretz.com/hasen/pages/ShArt.jhtml?itemNo=573295 Idit Avrahami, Nurit Wurgaft, "Naomi Shemer had no reason to feel bad, says Basque singer"] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20120629142103/http://www.haaretz.com/news/naomi-shemer-had-no-reason-to-feel-bad-says-basque-singer-1.157926 |date=2012-06-29 }}, ''Haaretz'', 6 May 2005, accessed 3 August 2012</ref>

